      "content": "That \"synchronization glitch\" angle sounds much better. It's much more manageable for the PR team. \n\nQuick follow up though—if a journalist actually asks for the root cause, like \"why did this sync glitch happen?\", do we tell them it was an S3 bucket misconfiguration? Or should we stick to the \"routine maintenance\" narrative and say it was just a temporary part of the system optimization process to avoid them digging into our actual backend security protocols?",
